# MotoBudget AI — Project Overview

Philippine-focused motorcycle trip budget planner with an AI Budget Assistant (Gemini).

## Stack

- **Frontend**: React 19, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS v4, Recharts, react-markdown
- **Backend**: Express (`server.ts`), Google GenAI SDK, Zod validation
- **Storage**: Client-side `localStorage` (`aistudio_moto_trips` key)
- **Secrets**: `GEMINI_API_KEY` in `.env` / AI Studio Secrets — server-side only, never client bundle

## Structure

```
server.ts              # Express API + Vite middleware (dev) or static (prod)
src/
  App.tsx              # Root state, localStorage, import/export
  types.ts             # TripBudget, expense types, presets
  validation.ts        # Zod schemas shared by server + client import
  components/          # TripForm, SavedTrips, AIAssistant, BudgetChart, TripComparer
```

## Commands

- `npm run dev` — start Express + Vite dev server (port 3000)
- `npm run build` — Vite client build + esbuild server bundle
- `npm run start` — production server
- `npm run lint` — `tsc --noEmit`

## Conventions

- Minimize scope; match existing dark UI (`#0A0A0A`, `#151515`, amber accents)
- Do not commit `.env` files or expose API keys
- Add validation in `src/validation.ts` for any new API or import fields
- Do not modify Vite HMR/watch config tied to `DISABLE_HMR` (AI Studio requirement)
